Teltoli rubbed her forehead again, feeling a headache coming on when 
Carnage said she should have listened to her mother. (Can bots even 
get headaches?)

"Yeah I guess. I could have been married to Ericson, that's my 
'betrothed'," She grimaced "been sitting at tables with countless 
numbers of forks and knives that you have to use, and on Cybertron"

The Fuzor shivered at a thundercrack, and folded her arms tighter. 
"But I think this planet is *way* more interesting.." She said 
sincerely.

Teltoli lifted her own eyebrow at Carnage at her reponse. "Really?" 
She asked. Her voice held a note of suspiscion in it, though. "That 
must make you pretty old.." She grinned, her mind whirling. Did 
Carnage really crash here? The Fuzor sensed something bigger had 
happened, but she didn't voice her thoughts.
